column2:
Seek the truth, hear the truth, learn the truth, love the truth, speak the truth, hold the truth and defend the truth until death.” - Jan Hus\n\nThe Bohemian government ordering its predominantly Czech army to crush the Elbian German separatists, after having declared their independence referendum to be illegal, proved to be a fatal error. Units across Bohemia mutinied, rallying instead to the Czech nationalists, who called upon the soldiers to see through the lies of their leaders, for the Czech people to see Bohemia for what it was : an oppressive German regime over a Slavic nation. These rebels marched on Prague, where they deposed the government and proclaimed a new, truly Czech state. All German territories once controlled by the old regime have disavowed Prague, either joining the Elbian Germans or going their own way. The last remnant of the Holy Roman Empire of the German Nation has been swept away by the will of the people.;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
CAESCA58.A;Pravda vítezí! (Truth prevails!);;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
CAESCA59.T;The Junker Restoration;;;;;;;;;;;;;
CAESCA59.D;The Danubian Federation’s radical liberalism has alarmed the Elbian nobility. It is no secret that the southerners see themselves as the leading candidates to unify Germany, but none of our Junkers have any desire for a liberal Germany. Thus they have decided to act. This morning a group of army officers, bolstered by far-right militias organized with Junker support, led their regiments into $CAPITAL$ and declared the formation of a new government! At the head of the coup d’etat was Count Maximilian Erwin von Aroldingen und Eltzingen, a man whose eloquence and aggressive personality has made up for his dynastic obscurity. He has now been crowned King Maximilian of the Elbian League, and seeks to herald a German rebirth fueled by conservative nationalism. It seems that the future clash between north and south shall be one of both geography and ideology.;;;;;;;;;;;;;
CAESCA59.A;Long live King Maximilian!;;;;;;;;;;;;;
CAESCA60.T;The Elbian Revolution;;;;;;;;;;;;;
CAESCA60.D;The Danubian Confederation’s far-right turn has alarmed the Elbian intelligentsia. It is no secret that the southerners see themselves as the leading candidate to unify Germany, but no liberal has any desire for a reactionary Germany. Thus they have decided to act. This morning a crowd of activists gathered outside the national legislature in $CAPITAL$, demanding a new constitution. Martial law was declared only for junior army officers to lead their regiments over to the liberals! Soon both the legislature and the executive mansion were stormed, and Radicalist revolutionaries led by author Gunther Rosenberg declared the creation of the League of Magdeburg. Rosenberg, acclaimed as Consul of the League (after Marinus Dahlke’s title), has declared that “Germany shall be whole, free, and she will be free - free of oppression, free of foreign occupation, and free of old idols and old tyrants.” It seems that the future clash between north and south shall be one of both geography and ideology.;;;;;;;;;;;;;
CAESCA60.A;1790 shall commence again!;;;;;;;;;;;;;
CAESCA61.T;The Elbian Constitutional Convention of $YEAR$;;;;;;;;;;;;;
CAESCA61.D;Dissatisfaction with our current political system on both the left and right has reached a boiling point when the Landtag voted to pass a law calling for a constitutional convention. Groups of liberals and conservatives have thus gathered in $CAPITAL$ to hammer out a new political vision. Paternalists have argued that extreme measures are necessary to defend against the Danubians, an argument which has failed to gain traction due to the southerners’ stable government. This morning a swath of paternalist delegates stormed out in disgust at the convention’s rejection of their proposals. It is rumored that they may be plotting with sympathetic members of the army to stage a coup d’etat and impose an absolute monarchy led by the charismatic Count Maximilian Erwin von Aroldingen und Eltzingen. If these are in fact just rumors then the main question is whether the liberals, led by author Gunther Rosenberg, will defend republicanism, or whether the conservatives will create a monarchy under Prince Werner von Amsberg.;;;;;;;;;;;;;
CAESCA61.A;The convention is dissolved by the paternalist coup!;;;;;;;;;;;;;
CAESCA61.B;Long live King Werner of the Elbian League!;;;;;;;;;;;;;
CAESCA61.C;Hail Chancellor Rosenberg of the League of Magdeburg!;;;;;;;;;;;;;
EVTNAME191915;The End of the Burgundian Civil War;;;;;;;;;;;
EVTDESC191915;The guns have fallen silent in Burgundy, and the struggle between the Royalists and the Parliamentarians has come to an end. Regardless of which side has prevailed, we must consider our foreign policy towards the Burgundians. We were allies before the civil war broke out, but this could be an opportunity to reevaluate our alignment if we feel that the victor of the civil war would not be an acceptable ally henceforth.;;;;;;;;;;;
EVTOPTA191915;Burgundy is still our ally.;;;;;;;;;;;
EVTOPTB191915;This alliance is no longer feasible.;;;;;;;;;;;
EVTNAME191916;The End of the Burgundian Civil War;;;;;;;;;;;
EVTDESC191916;The guns have fallen silent in Burgundy, and the struggle between the Royalists and the Parliamentarians has come to an end. Regardless of which side has prevailed, we must consider our foreign policy towards the Burgundians. We had close political and economic ties to Burgundy before the civil war broke out, but this could be an opportunity to reevaluate our alignment if we feel that the victor of the civil war would not be an acceptable protector henceforth.;;;;;;;;;;; 
EVTOPTA191916;Burgundy is still our best choice of guardian.;;;;;;;;;;; 
EVTOPTB191916;Let us be allies, not servants, of Burgundy.;;;;;;;;;;; 
EVTOPTC191916;These arrangements are no longer feasible.;;;;;;;;;;;
#DECISIONS;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
invite_saxon_tags_title;Hegemony over the Elbians;;;;;;;;;;;;;x,,,,,,,, 
invite_saxon_tags_desc;Our political dominance in northern Germany has given us the opportunity to assume a stronger position of leadership over the disparate states of the region. Foreign powers such as Scandinavia are eager to take control of these vulnerable realms for their own interests. They will surely understand the need of our protection - especially if we explain to them our plan for a greater union of northern Germans.;;;;;;;;;;;;;x,,,,,,,,
delete_NGF_title;Liberate the Elbians!;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
delete_NGF_desc;The Elbian German client state which Scandinavia had established in northern Germany to prepare the region for further integration has, through unexpected means, broken free of its bonds. This illegitimate creation of Kopenhagen is a blight upon Europe, created only for the sake of a foreign invader, and so we must strike them down! Their people shall greet us as liberators.;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
#GERMAN MINORS - Swabia, Rhineland and Franconia;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER1.T;The Eidgenossenschaftgespenst;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER1.D;The Confederacy proudly stands as an enduring “alliance” of cantons composed of various entities having greater autonomy in the Reich. Despite such developments, political analysts and observers consider the state as a ‘spectre’, a “Eidgenossenschaftgespenst”, torn apart by years of internal turmoil and meddling by foreign powers that left it in a limbo. Such examples are the Western cantons under Burgundy’s sphere and the Graubunden (Grey Leagues) to the east being a longtime ally of the Confederacy since the 15th century. Despite their nominally independent status, they are considered “associates” with their historically amicable ties with Zurich. Many liberals in the Tagsatzung have argued that a “Swiss” identity is the solution to mend the wounds of our state. With Imperial encroachment on the rise and pan-German radicals at our doorstep, the Swiss must live up to its destiny and best its rivals through wit or by force, lest we succumb to the whims of Great powers or German upstarts in the region.;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER1.A;Einer für alle? Alle für einen?;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER2.T;The Western Cantons’ Referendum of $YEAR$;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER2.D;The Western cantons, notably the areas under the jurisdiction of Basel and Fribourg are nominally under the influence of Anvers but are longtime associates of the Swiss Confederacy. After experiencing the carnage of the Great German War, most of its war-weary inhabitants have longed for unity with Zurich fearing that another war would “tear comrades apart and bring upon the never-ending sorrow of mothers.” In a recent plebiscite held in both counties  this year, Bern and Freiburg have voted 97% and 99% respectively to become full-fledged cantons of the Confederation. Despite celebrations erupting in the Confederacy welcoming their new brothers, the jubilant mood is dampened with the fact that Anvers, while still silent on the matter, has the final word on these affairs, and may force “special conditions'' outright that may infringe on our sovereignty!;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER2.A;Those perfidious Burgundians!;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER3.T;The Western Cantons’ Plea;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER3.D;A new development has begun brewing in the borderlands of the Alps. The Cantons of Basel and Fribourg have overwhelmingly voted for their admission to the Swiss Confederacy. While using direct force against them would invoke Prague’s wrath, we still exert significant influence over said counties. With such matters in mind, we can spin this debacle to our advantage. We could offer Zurich the two counties in exchange for “reassurances'', putting the Swiss firmly under our influence, or shall we opt to send in the army with haste before the bill is ratified, rendering the referendum null and void in practice? §RSurely we won’t possibly provoke the locals to engage in radical activity and embolden the revolutionaries in doing the former, right?§;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER3.A;So long as the Swiss reassures its alignment with us.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER3.B;Oh well. How about no?;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER4.T;The Slaughter in the Western Cantons;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER4.D;The inevitable has begun. The Burgundians, fearing a resurgent Swiss Confederacy giving Bohemia leverage in Alpine affairs, were quick to dispatch the 6eme Corps d’Armee in Geneva to Basel and Fribourg to pressure the counties to reject the bill and block the annexation of these territories. Brawls between the occupiers and locals have begun erupting, with reports of casualties, revolutionary involvement, and even reprisals on both sides. Many of our citizens have derided the government on this affair, which resulted in an upsurge of revolutionary and radical sentiment in the “occupied” cantons and within the Confederacy!.;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER4.A;We will not forget this!;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER5.T;An Offer from Burgundy;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER5.D;An envoy from Anvers has arrived in Zurich, offering us the “complete” and “absolute” support of the admission of Basel and Fribourg into the Confederacy. In return, the Burgundians have requested “reassurances” from us, urging that we would “stay out” of imperial affairs for an unspecified period of time (and nature) and instead enter security treaties and a customs union with Anvers. While liberal radicals and revolutionaries in the Tagsatzung consider this as an “opportunistic” move and a “betrayal” of national interests, conservatives and the Rheintreue (the pro-Burgundian faction) alike have seen the potential economic prospects with Burgundy appealing, even more so than Prague already did to us for the past hundred years.;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER5.A;We accept.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER5.B;We decline.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER6.T;The Confederacy Stands Defiant!;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER6.D;Despite our diplomatic overtures towards the Swiss, it appears that they have outright rejected our most humble and interesting proposal! Of course, we were quick to mete this disgrace with force: we were quick to dispatch the 6eme Corps d’Armee in Geneva to Basel and Fribourg to quell dissent outright and block any attempts of collusion with rogue revolutionaries in Zurich. Despite reports of infighting with perceived ‘insurgents’ aligned with the radical “Helvetic Society'' and brawls with the locals which have resulted in casualties, hopefully we were right in convincing them who is the boss of the Alps.;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER6.A;If those greedy bankers want to rot with Prague, then so be it!;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER7.T;The Swiss Demand our Annexation!;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER7.D;The Swiss Confederacy have requested we abide by the “will of the people”, that is the irrevocable and absolute annexation of $COUNTRY$ to the Swiss Confederacy! That is unless reactionary elements were to immediately storm the town halls and instill that we remain independent and maintain our sovereignty as usual!;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER7.A;We welcome our brothers!;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER7.B;Oh, look, a bird!;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER8.T;The Failure of the Graubund;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER8.D;The counter-coup has happened;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER8.A;Oh no…Swissbros…;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER9.T;Chaos in the Tagsatzung;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER9.D;The demise of the Holy Roman Empire meant that the calls of German unity have dramatically shaken the foundations of our country to its roots. Despite masses welcoming the end of an era, the dissolution of the old Imperial order brought political instability to the country of the highest levels never seen before, intensified with the fears of famine. The Tagsatzung is on edge, furiously debating and scheming on how the country shall move forward from this abrupt development, be it through subservience with the Burgundians, “unity” with the Danubians pressured by Pan-Germanists in the diet, or the pursuit of further reform - dissolving the Tagsatzung for an National Assembly culminating in the establishment of a full fledged unitary democracy modeled after Etruria. With the dust starting to settle, the final convocation of the Tagsatzung on this day shall decide the fate of the Swiss nation!;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER9.A;We will see what shall become of our fate.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER10.T;The Nationale Schutzregierung of $YEAR$;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER10.D;Many elements of the Landesmiliz in the Aktientheater - the meeting place of the Tagsatzung in Zürich, have been long weary and sick of the hourly tirades that resonated the walls of the building within. This feeling of unease was shattered with a sudden thud from the backside of the building: it appears that a rogue faction of the Army has overrun Zurich, occupying key government buildings without any resistance whatsoever even from the Landesmiliz. This faction, led by Generalfeldmarschall Wilhelm Dufour, a veteran of the Great German War aligned with the Danubian cause, announced their intentions to instill a “military government” in light of the impending Burgundian threat. Despite their noble intentions, they were outed as Danubian loyalists by radicals and revolutionaries alike, conspiring with the Pan-German cause. Order is restored - at the cost of burying the Helvetic dream in the dust.;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER10.A;”Platz machen!”;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER11.T;The Revolutionary Swiss Republic;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER11.D;The atmosphere inside the halls of the Aktientheater - the meeting place of the Tagsatzung, were more or less unsettling with the hourly tirades that resonated within. The bickering ceased when an official approached the podium, proclaiming that there was a failed “coup attempt” moments ago by pro-Danubian loyalists, thwarted thanks to the efforts of revolutionary militias and city folk in a rare, bloodless struggle. The liberal and revolutionary deputies erupted in jubilation, whilst pro-Danubian conservatives and Burgunders smirked and left in protest. With the support of radicals, liberals and revolutionaries regardless of affiliation, have unanimously proclaimed the establishment of a new, unitary “Revolutionary Swiss Republic'' that shall hopefully carry on Dahlke and the 91ers’ legacy. The beacon of liberty shines on the majestic peaks of the Alps!.;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER11.A;The voice of the people, the voice of God.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER12.T;The Natural Conclusion;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER12.D;The atmosphere inside the halls of the Aktientheater - the meeting place of the Tagsatzung, were more or less unsettling with the hourly tirades that resonated within. As the chaotic bickering comes to a close in the afternoon, the Aktientheater is filled with gloomy faces, most present from the liberals and the revolutionary delegates. Many were shocked that the Rheintreue and the conservatives have stood out. However as soon as the vote has been delivered, the assembly again erupts into chaos, with the matter at hand devoted to the preservation of the “old order” or the wild prospect from Rheintreue reactionaries and noblemen in giving the title of Duchy of Schweiz bound by “union” with Friedrich III of Baden, noted for his ambitious reactionary zeal and his sympathies with the Jeanist cause in Anvers. In the end only one faction stands out.;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER12.A;The Rheintreue prevail - establishing the Duchy of Schweiz;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER12.B;Maintain the Status Quo - The Confederacy endures.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER13.T;The Seizure of Ulm;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER13.D;The rapid deterioration of the situation in Ulm, following the collapse of Bavarian authority in their loss in the Donaubrüderkrieg meant that our forces were able to seize the opportunity - instilling order in the city. Despite accounts of bickering from the locals, the occupation was mostly peaceful, and the Mayor of Ulm has announced his loyalties and allegiances to our monarch, ensuring that Ulm will be forever Wurttemberger!;;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER13.A;Another Contender to the Swabian Claim?;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER14.T;The Danubian Accord on Ulm, $YEAR$;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER14.D;With Ulm crucial to the Danubian cause knowing that will certainly strengthen our claim to the German throne, they have immediately jumped on this opportunity and claimed the lonely “free” city to themselves! With the country being deprived of Imperial immediacy, they are now helpless. With the Emperor’s attention completely divided, there is nobody to stop us!;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER14.A;A noble ending for a “free” city?;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER15.T;Interference from Anvers!;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER15.D;With the Burgundians firmly entrenched in their prerogative to resurrect the Stem Duchy under the “noble” wing of the house of Bouillon, the Monarch, avoiding war with the bellicose neighbor,  has no choice but to accede to the demands of Anvers, putting the fate of the Swabian project under the machinations of the Jeanist cause.;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER15.A;A disgraceful yet necessary agreement.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER16.T;The Proud Torchbearer of the Swabian Dream;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER16.D;The Duchy of Württemberg stood for nearly 800 years as the predominant Catholic hegemon of the Swabian Imperial Circle. it has withstood tumultuous decades of religious strife and internal turmoil. Still, the memory of the Great German War still remains fresh in its citizens, ever weary of Prague’s influence and the revolutionary spirit still lingering. Despite nostalgia for the revival of the old Stem Duchy up nigh, the Swabian Lion must prove itself worthy. The current monarch, Wilhelm I, having witnessed the Coalition Wars tearing his demesne apart, has urged for a more “independent” footing among the other states in the Reich, and from the Burgundian titan as well, at times even fervent to the idea of the revival of a Swabian “Kingdom”. Whatever happens next surely depends on how Prague reacts to the impending maelstrom, which can affect us profoundly in the years to come.;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER16.A;We march into the world, fearless and true!;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER17.T;A “Revolutionary War” for Swabia?;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER17.D;War has erupted in Burgundy between the dissenting liberal factions of the Parliament in Anvers and the reactionary royalists devoted to the cause of Jean VI! This is a window of opportunity for us - and as such the National Assembly has convened on the next course of action. The bellicose and radical Pan-German faction insists that we capitalize on this - committing ourselves to a sweeping expeditionary campaign against Württemberg. On the other hand, the non-interventionist Cliques, representing business owners and the old order, sought for neutrality in the conflict. After hours of usual cutthroat debates and tirades on both sides, only the gavel’s pall decides the course of action. §RHowever, we must be wary as a resurgent Württemberg might entail open conflict irregardless of our approach.§;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER17.A;The Liberals succeed - the National Council gears up for war;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER17.B;The Non-Interventionists proclaim neutrality.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER18.T;News from the Swiss Frontier;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER18.D;With the Burgundian Civil War still reeling, the inevitable has happened: reports of $FROMCOUNTRY_ADJ$ forces overwhelming border posts along the $THISCOUNTRY_ADJ$ border en masse, reminiscent of the tactics seen in the Great German War, even capturing numerous towns along the frontier in the process! The $THISCOUNTRY_ADJ$ army has begun mobilizing its forces to meet the revolutionary bastards in battle. With the Duchy already proclaiming its intentions to resurrect the Stem Duchy once more, it appears that the Swabian Lion is ready to pounce on its enemies to fulfill its destiny.;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER18.A;We shall bring these unruly Helvetics to the fold!;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER19.T;News from the Swiss Frontier;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER19.D;With the Burgundian Civil War still reeling, the inevitable has happened: reports of $FROM_COUNTRY_ADJ$ forces overwhelming border posts along the $THISCOUNTRY_ADJ$ border en masse, reminiscent of the tactics seen in the Great German War, even capturing numerous towns along the frontier in the process! The $THISCOUNTRY_ADJ$ army has begun mobilizing its forces to meet the revolutionary bastards in battle. May our soldiers be blessed in battle, for God and Country!;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER19.A;May God help us all!;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER20.T;The Unterwerfungskrieg;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER20.D;Our ambitions are slowly being brought to fruition! With the outbreak of civil war in Burgundy, they have been rendered powerless in intervening in the affairs of their spherelings. This timing is crucial! With the Swiss rendered vulnerable in the conflict, we can now finally subjugate them once and for all, avenging the setbacks of the Staufers in the XIIth century. This is an opportunity to make our mark and be worthy of the title of “King of Swabia”!;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER20.A;We shall bring these unruly Helvetics to the fold!;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER20.B;A land war in the Alps? Probably not worth it;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER21.T;The Unterwerfungskrieg;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER21.D;”You still have sons,\nLike St. Jacob saw them,\nJoyfully hasten to the battle.”\n- Excerpt from ‘Rufst du, mein Vaterland’\n\nWe have received reports of $FROM_COUNTRY_ADJ$ forces massing on the frontier, with the sole goal reviving the olden Stem Duchy of Swabia through the outright subjugation of all Swabian states! As fearless the Swabian lion may be, none can fear the forces of brotherhood and fraternity that will smite any foe that dares trespass the free and sacred peaks of the Alps!;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER21.A;We’ll make sure that they’ll pay dearly.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER210.T;The West Alpine War;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER210.D;The ongoing chaos amongst the Swabian states has deprived us of foreign protection. This has not gone unnoticed by the Swiss, who have now declared war to force us into their confederation! We must make a stand in the name of cantonal liberty.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER210.A;The mountains shall be their graves!;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER22.T;The Matter of the Duchy of Baden;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER22.D;Baden is historically one of the most problematic states in the Reich and the German periphery. Sharing a border with the Burgundian behemoth, it always fell victim to the whims of Anvers despite nominally being a part of the Swabian Circle. Their monarch, Friedrich Wilhelm III, despite having sympathies to the Burgundian Crown (and some anti-monarchist gossip tabloids in Germany describing him as a closet Jeanist by heart), is still a threat to be reckoned with and has recently pronounced his support for the formation of Swabia. With the Burgundians still in turmoil with their civil war, it is now high time we conclude the campaign to unite the Swabian peoples into one banner! Let us do it with haste, however, since Anvers may intervene if we act slothful in this conflict.;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER22.A;$THISCOUNTRY_ADJ$ brethren, to battle! For Swabia!;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER22.B;Its best that we hunker down so as not to provoke the beast;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER23.T;Burgundy Enforces Peace!;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER23.D;With our war torn country being back in one piece, it is now time that we deal with the Swabian threat. The upstarts have torn apart the Treaties of Zurich, which was formulated in 1821 amidst the War of the 4th Coalition that had stipulations that prohibited any open conflict between any of the states that encompass the former Swabian Circle. Those ambitious opportunists, however, have used the abrupt loss of diplomatic authority to reform the old stem Duchy without any consent from Anvers. We must enforce the Treaties of Zurich and restore order to the unruly states in Swabia, for we cannot allow another threat to meddle in our affairs (and ambitions) in the Rhine.;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER23.A;The Treaties of Zurich must be enforced!;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER24.T;Burgundy Demands we Uphold the Treaties of Zurich!;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER24.D;With the Burgundian government successfully emerging victorious after their civil war, we were met with reports that the Burgundian military was amassing soldiers to our borders. At the same time, an envoy from Anvers has sent our $MONARCHTITLE$ a word of warning, demanding that we stay true to the 1821 Treaties of Zurich - ceasing all conflicts with our neighbors and rescind all our illegal territorial gains in Swabia! As our armies are no match against the Burgundians, unprepared even, in fighting a two front war, we have no choice but to abandon our claims and uphold the treaties.;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER24.A;Damn!;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER25.T;The Swabian Affair;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER25.D;The lands of the former Swabian Circles have always been vital to the fulfillment of the Donaulicherehrgeiz, and for the eventual formation of a unified German state. However the Swabian states were always subject to Burgundian repercussions despite historically being a nominal part of the former Reich. The Hollowing, combined with the upsurge in revolutionary sentiment had further destabilized the area - altering the political landscape in the region tremendously. With Burgundy having recovered from a brief yet chaotic civil war, we can now begin negotiations with the Burgundians on the status of the Swabian states.;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER25.A;A deal with the devil? Don’t mind if I do.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER26.T;The Stuttgart Conference of $YEAR$;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER26.D;The newly established Süddeutscher Bund, brimming with ambition to fulfill the Donaulicherehrgeiz (Danubian ambition), has set its sights on its unruly western neighbors: the states of the former Swabian Circle in southwest Germany. Not wishing to provoke a costly conflict with Burgundy which still has an immense sway in Swabian affairs and the entirety of Germany still struggling with the effects of the Hollowing, the Danubian government has opted to mediate the issue with the Burgundians in a high profile meeting at Stuttgart.\nAnalysts and observers welcomed the development gladly but remained cautious. They all agree that the result of the conference depends on the allegiances of Swabian states - despite claims from Danubian and Burgundian outlets touting this as a “deal of the century”, open war is still a distinct possibility should either side fail to keep one’s side of the bargain.;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER26.A;Hopefully things won't go south;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER27.T;The Stuttgart Conference - The $COUNTRY_ADJ$ Question;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER27.D;The two behemoths bordering our lands have come knocking at our doorstep. With a resurgent South German Confederation and the Burgundians recovered from their civil war, they have politely approached us to finally mediate the Swabian Question once and for all in Stuttgart. So far, our monarch has longed for a neutral approach to the matter while the pro-Burgundian Rheintreue elite and pro-Danubian conservatives are still at large in the Landtag. The “day of decision” has come, and the following days will decide our country’s destiny - be it either under the Burgundian jackboot or even of neutrality, perhaps?;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER27.A;We must side with the Danubians!;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER27.B;We shall remain neutral.;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER27.C;Side with Burgundy;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER28.T;The Stuttgart Conference - The $COUNTRY_ADJ$ Question;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER28.D;The two behemoths bordering our lands have come knocking at our doorstep. With a resurgent South German Confederation and the Burgundians recovered from their civil war, they have politely approached us to finally mediate the Swabian Question once and for all in Stuttgart. Despite the tumultuous effects of the Hollowing is, luckily, still intact and in one piece. Our country’s destiny, of course lies on those who handle it, and ultimately their loyalties:;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER28.A;The Schutzregierung pronounces its support for the Bund!;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER28.B;The National Council declares neutrality.;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER28.C;The Rheintreue sides with Burgundy!;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER29.T;The Stuttgart Conference - Burgundian Dominance;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER29.D;Our country is now in shambles : despite being nominally independent in the eyes of the world, our current political trajectory means that we are fated for the worst. Despite our best efforts, the $MONARCHTITLE$ is defenseless either to continual Burgundian subversion and influence, or be forced to the fold amidst recent defeats following a disastrous conflict with the Burgundians. We have no choice but to ultimately enter a series of “friendship” treaties with Anvers which will surely cost us our sovereignty in the long term.;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER29.A;The Rheintreue fanatics finally got their wish…;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER30.T;The Stuttgart Conference - Bedingung A.II;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER30.D;”The Respective Heads of State of the Kingdom of Burgundy and the Danubian Confederation come in mutual agreement in the matter as follows : With the Swabian situation rendered untenable due to the lack of ‘order’ and ‘discipline’ within the vicinity, a special case shall be laid therewith, that shall instill immediate order to the region with haste. Both parties have reciprocally agreed that a military intervention is in order, seeing that no further negotiation would be possible other than the use of force.”\n\nThe unthinkable has begun. We must now act at once! There is no turning back for the defense of the Swabian cause.;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER30.A;Die Zeit ist nah, Brüder!;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER31.T;Burgundy Dominant in the Stuttgart Conference!;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER31.D;With the Stuttgart Conference coming to a close, it appears that the Burgundian delegation has stood overwhelmingly victorious, proclaiming that the entirety of Swabia is now under the “safe hands” of the Burgundians. As an insult, they have asked us to “respect their and the Swabian people’s decision”. The Danubian delegation was outraged, and has since appealed to the King for mediation on the issue! The public is outraged with these developments, demanding that we take action by “taking matters into our own hands”. We shouldn’t be worthy of being called the Danubian Confederation if we couldn’t even liberate the oppressed peoples of Swabia, right?;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
MGER31.A;We can’t openly enter into conflict - Concede.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MGER31.B;Respekt?" Als ob! Wir fahren nach Antwerpen!
